arts.ttl: World Cup qualifying draw seedings in Europe completed by Slovakia, Czech wins in Nations League
arts.sum: The draw seedings for 2026 World Cup qualifying groups in Europe were decided Tuesday when the last round of Nations League games saw Slovakia and the Czech Republic secure a higher status. Europe has 16 entries in the first 48-team World Cup and the other four places will be decided by playoff knockout brackets in March 2026.

arts.ttl: Emma Raducanu wins singles tie but Britain beaten in Billie Jean King Cup semi-final against Slovakia
arts.sum: Emma Raducanu got Team GB off to a winning start when defeating Viktoria Hruncakova 6-4 6-4 - her third consecutive straight-sets win in the Finals - but British No 1 Katie Boulter was beaten in the second singles rubber and Slovakia claimed the decisive doubles match. Despite taking the opening set against world No 43 Rebecca Sramkova, Boulter went down 2-6 6-4 6-4, before Olivia Nicholls and Heather Watson were roundly beaten 6-2 6-2 by Hruncakova and Tereza Mihalikova in the doubles.

arts.ttl: Emma Raducanu wins in Billie Jean King Cup as Great Britain take charge of Slovakia semi-final
arts.sum: Raducanu - who triumphed in straight sets in Britain's prior wins over Germany and defending-champions Canada - came flying out of the blocks against Hruncakova, immediately breaking the world No 238. arts.ttl: Juventus eye Skriniar, PSG Interested in Fagioli
arts.sum: Juventus are actively seeking a central defender for the upcoming January transfer window, with Milan Skriniar emerging as the top target. The 30-year-old Slovak international, formerly of Inter Milan, is currently under contract with Paris Saint-Germain until June 2028. Despite his lucrative contract, which sees him earn approximately 8 million euros net per season plus bonuses, Skriniar has struggled to secure regular playing time under coach Luis Enrique. The player has already expressed his willingness to return to Italy, preferably not on a short-term six-month loan deal. arts.ttl: Farmers, local beers & a three-day journey - watching Estonia away
arts.sum: Azerbaijan away proves to be a great adventure for Englishman Mark Corbett as he cheers on Estonia in a Nations League tie.
